# Part 2 — Describe a challenging technological problem you faced

One challenging technological problem I faced happened last semester when I was working on a small AI-related programming project with my classmates. We were trying to build a simple web-based chatbot, and my responsibility was to connect the backend AI model with the front-end interface. At first, I thought it would be fairly straightforward, but it turned out to be much more complicated than I expected.

The main problem was that the server kept crashing whenever multiple users accessed the chatbot at the same time. Sometimes the responses were delayed for several seconds, and occasionally the whole webpage would freeze completely. This happened in our university dormitory while we were preparing for a project presentation, so the pressure was extremely high because we only had a few days left before the deadline.

What made it especially challenging was that we couldn’t immediately identify the source of the problem. At first, we thought it was caused by the AI model itself, but later we realized the issue was related to memory management and inefficient API requests. Since I’m still a student and not an experienced software engineer, debugging the system took a lot of patience and research. I spent hours reading technical forums, watching YouTube tutorials, and testing different solutions line by line.

Eventually, I solved the problem by optimizing the request process and reducing unnecessary data transmission between the front end and the backend. I also added a caching mechanism and improved the server configuration. After several rounds of testing, the chatbot finally became stable enough for our presentation.

Although the experience was stressful, I actually learned a lot from it. It taught me that technological problems often require logical thinking, teamwork, and persistence rather than just technical knowledge alone. In a way, it also made me more confident in dealing with complex programming challenges in the future.

---

### 中文翻译：

我遇到过一个很有挑战性的科技问题，那是在上学期我和同学一起做一个人工智能相关的小项目时发生的。我们当时在开发一个基于网页的聊天机器人，而我的任务是把后端 AI 模型和前端界面连接起来。一开始我觉得这个工作应该比较简单，但后来发现比我想象中复杂得多。

主要的问题是，当多个用户同时访问聊天机器人时，服务器会不断崩溃。有时候回复会延迟好几秒，甚至整个网页会直接卡死。这件事发生在我们准备项目展示的时候，当时我们在大学宿舍里调试程序，而距离截止日期只剩下几天，所以压力特别大。

最困难的一点是，我们一开始根本找不到问题来源。最初我们以为是 AI 模型本身导致的，但后来才发现问题实际上与内存管理以及低效的 API 请求有关。因为我毕竟还是学生，并不是经验丰富的软件工程师，所以整个调试过程花费了很多耐心和研究时间。我花了好几个小时查技术论坛、看 YouTube 教程，并且一行一行地测试不同解决方案。

最后，我通过优化请求流程、减少前后端之间不必要的数据传输解决了问题。我还加入了缓存机制，并优化了服务器配置。经过多轮测试之后，聊天机器人终于稳定下来，顺利完成了展示。

虽然整个过程很有压力，但我确实学到了很多东西。它让我明白，解决科技问题不仅需要技术知识，更需要逻辑思维、团队合作以及坚持不懈的精神。从某种意义上来说，这次经历也让我对未来面对复杂编程挑战更有信心了。

